{
  "stem": "12462.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Tom Dodd decided that they had to allow the Soviets to have some cross-examination.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Since they produced him as a defendant, why not let the Soviets cross-examine him?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And among other things, Fritzsche denied the so-called Fritzsche confession, which they had obtained from him just after they'd captured him, long before the trial.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I refused to use it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I did not-- I declined to use that during my presentation, which was much earlier than the Soviet case, of course.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Partly because of the language in it, and partly because, in dealing with the defense counsel, I was getting these other statements, partly with an understanding that, if I thought Fritzsche was giving me a fair amount of data, even though he was trying to explain it, that I wouldn't use the confession.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this is a kind of a-- [CLEARS THROAT] an arrangement between the defense counsel and the prosecution counsel, which was approved by Colonel Storey.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, as they were so glad to see some evidence concerning one of the defendants, which wasn't involved in that, quote, Soviet confession, that I-- that's one reason I was then assigned to the Schirach case as well.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'm the only assistant trial counsel, actually, that presented two of the cases against the defendants.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] He wrote a book, called-- I've got it in the other room.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He wrote a book, in which he tried to kind of explain his-- why he'd done things.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was contrite, to an extent.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] He talked about his life in jail, and about his experiences, and et cetera.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It isn't a very impressive book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He does translate it in to English.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't think it sold very-- people weren't too interested in it.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
